\title{psAve: Model-Averaged Propensity Scores Selected by Prognostic-Score Balance}
\description{
Constructs a model-averaged propensity score as a convex combination of
candidate propensity score models, with mixing weights selected on a
simplex grid to optimize covariate or prognostic-score balance,
implementing the method of Kabata, Stuart and Shintani (2024). Prognostic
scores follow Hansen (2008): outcome models are fit on untreated units
only. The resulting score is designed to be supplied directly to
\code{\link[MatchIt:matchit]{MatchIt::matchit()}} as a distance measure or to \code{\link[WeightIt:weightit]{WeightIt::weightit()}} as
a propensity score, with balance assessment via \pkg{cobalt}.
}
\details{
The single estimation function is \code{\link[=psave]{psave()}}. Its result hands off to the
existing ecosystem: \code{\link[=psave_match]{psave_match()}} / \code{\link[=psave_weight]{psave_weight()}} (or the equivalent
explicit \code{\link[MatchIt:matchit]{MatchIt::matchit()}} / \code{\link[WeightIt:weightit]{WeightIt::weightit()}} calls),
\code{\link[cobalt:bal.tab]{cobalt::bal.tab()}} (which has a method for \code{psave} objects), and effect
estimation with the tools you already use (\pkg{survey},
\pkg{marginaleffects}, ...). Utilities \code{\link[=simplex_grid]{simplex_grid()}} and
\code{\link[=psave_criteria]{psave_criteria()}} expose the grid enumeration and the selection criteria
for methods research and testing. See \link{psave-details} for the differences
from the paper's reference implementation.
}
